    • Uses of BatchBuilder in batch

      Methods in batch that return BatchBuilder 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.debug(boolean debug)
      Enables or disables the debug mode.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.descending(boolean desc)
      Enables a flag to sort the copied images in descending order.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.embedDateTime(boolean emb)
      Appends the date and time attribute to each image file name.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.fileSet(java.lang.String[] files)
      Specifies a list of individual image files to copy, instead of copying all files in the source directory.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.name(java.lang.String prefix)
      Sets a prefix to be prepended to each output image file name.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.skipVideo(boolean media)
      Determines whether media files should be ignored or copied.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.source(java.lang.String src)
      Sets the source directory containing original image files.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.target(java.lang.String target)
      Sets the target directory where copied image files are saved to.
      BatchBuilder BatchBuilder.userDate(java.lang.String dt)
      Sets the date and time to modify the Date Taken attribute.
      Constructors in batch with parameters of type BatchBuilder 
      Constructor Description
      BatchConsole(BatchBuilder builder)
      Constructs a console interface, using a Builder design pattern to process the parameters and update the copied image files.
      BatchExecutor(BatchBuilder builder)
      Constructs a BatchExecutor using the provided BatchBuilder configuration.
